title.narrative: STRENGTHENED CAPACITY FOR MCH, DEVELOPMENT AND ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH

description.narrative: By 2025 designated government agencies have increased capacity to collect, analyze and use data to inform decision-making, and have strengthened capacity to address mother and child health, development and environmental health needs., which contributes to Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Environmental Sustainability, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025 designated government agencies have increased capacity to collect, analyze and use data to inform decision-making, and have strengthened capacity to address mother and child health, development and environmental health needs.
